commit.message: Make library versioned on Windows too
Add missing license files to distribution tarball

libpaper.c: always #include relocatable.h (fix #57)

If weâ€™re not using relocation, we need it to define macros for unused
symbols.
Update licenses of libpaper files to include MIT license where appropriate
paper.h: update notice about backwards compatibility

Remove LGPLed code from the library (except for relocation code)

Add my own code to implement strndup, getln (replaces getline) and
file_join (replaces mfile_name_concat).

This means that I can relicense the library under the MIT license provided
that it is compiled without relocation support.
configure.ac: move AC_USE_SYSTEM_EXTENSIONS earlier to avoid a warning

Fix generation of paperspecs(5)

Like paper(1), paperspecs(5) contains paths that need to be expanded at make
time, not configure time.

commit.message:
Tests: Set DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH (fix #52)

This allows the tests to find the just-built copy of libpaper.dylib on
macOS when not using --enable-relocatable.
bootstrap.conf: remove unused pathmax and unneeded strcase

bootstrap.conf: relocatable-script is no longer needed

(It was used for paperconfig)
